    <h1>Meet LNR</h1>
    <p>A Glimpse into the Mind and Journey of Prof. R. Lakshmi Narayan</p>
  </header>

  <div class="container">
    <div class="profile">
      <img src="your-image-path.jpg" alt="Prof. R. Lakshmi Narayan">
      <div class="bio">
        <h2>Prof. R. Lakshmi Narayan</h2>
        <p>Hello! I'm Lakshmi — a curious mind with a passion for materials science, and a firm believer in learning by doing. My journey has taken me across academic institutions, industry collaborations, and international symposia, but at the heart of it all lies one goal: to ignite curiosity and critical thinking in young minds.</p>
        <p>I currently serve as a faculty member at the Department of Materials Science and Engineering, IIT Delhi. I work at the exciting intersection of metal additive manufacturing, microstructure–property relationships, and advanced characterization.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="quote-box">
      “To me, science is not about answers—it’s about asking the right questions, and daring to explore the unknown with integrity and imagination.”
    </div>

    <div class="section">
      <h3>My Teaching Philosophy</h3>
      <p>Teaching, to me, is more than delivering lectures—it's about mentorship, dialogue, and mutual growth. I strive to create a space where questions are welcomed, mistakes are seen as learning milestones, and students are encouraged to challenge even the fundamentals.</p>
      <p>Whether it’s in the lab or the classroom, I believe in learning by doing. I design courses and projects that bring theory to life—giving students the opportunity to build, break, analyze, and discover.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
      <h3>What Drives Me</h3>
      <p>Every alloy has a story, every micrograph a message. I find joy in interpreting those stories—be it through fracture surfaces, diffusion gradients, or phase maps. My research is driven by a desire to understand how structure governs behavior, and how we can use that understanding to engineer better materials.</p>
      <p>I also deeply enjoy collaborative research—my work spans multiple countries, disciplines, and industries. I’ve been privileged to guide young researchers who have gone on to make significant contributions of their own.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
      <h3>Beyond the Lab</h3>
      <p>When I’m not peering into a microscope or scribbling in my research notebook, you’ll find me enjoying Carnatic music, taking long nature walks, or catching up on philosophy and history books.</p>
      <p>Ultimately, I believe science is a human endeavor—rooted in humility, shaped by community, and propelled by wonder.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
